  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb\u0dda\u0da7 \u0d91\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba \u0dc3\u0da2\u0db6 \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0dcf \u0daf\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sajaba condemns the attack on Antare",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Samagi Jana Balavega General Secretary Ranjith Maddumbandara said that he strongly condemns the tear gas and water attack by the police on the students of the Inter-University Student Union who were engaged in a solidarity demonstration and protest.",
        "The Secretary General has confirmed again and again that there is a serious contradiction between what the government led by the President is saying and what is being implemented.",
        "\"The President continued to emphasize inside and outside the parliament that there will be no obstacles for peaceful protests. But what is happening is how the democratic rights, such as freedom of speech and assembly, which are held responsible and accountable by the constitution and international conventions, are being suppressed under the emergency law. The government has failed to present any justifiable reason for this repression.",
        "In this protest, the protesting students demanded that the universities be opened immediately and that a suitable economic program be prepared for the people of the country to live and that steps be taken to free the country from the obstacles to pursue the professions of life freely. It is clear in the repression implemented by the government, which does not respond to those demands, that a hidden agenda is at work in this process. We believe that all this is guided by an invisible hand. It is very clear that the attempt was made to anesthetize the protests against the government by instilling fear in the society through such actions.",
        "It is clear that all these are measures to consolidate the power of the government led by the minor president, which provokes public opposition and anger, and do not provide solutions to the basic crises of the country.",
        "The President, who declared that the emergency law will be abolished immediately, sees the contradiction between the statement and the action in the summoning of the Triwida Army to seven districts through a special gazette announcement.",
        "We urge the government to immediately withdraw all the processes that curtail the basic rights of the people of the country and suppress the freedom of expression guaranteed by the constitution. We also ask the government led by the President to immediately release the student activists who are detained on detention orders."
      ],
